---
description: Security baseline policy
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never hardcode secrets.
- Validate external input at API boundaries.
- Keep dependencies updated and audit regularly.
- Apply least privilege for runtime and CI tokens.
- Require auth/authorization checks for mutating API routes unless explicitly public by design.
- Validate input before business logic and return consistent, non-sensitive error responses.

## Example

```ts
// Good: validates input and avoids leaking internals.
if (!session?.user?.id) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });
}
const parsed = schema.safeParse(body);
if (!parsed.success) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: "Invalid request payload" }, { status: 400 });
}

// Bad: hardcoded secret and raw error leakage.
const apiKey = "sk_live_123"; // never hardcode secrets
return NextResponse.json({ error: String(err) }, { status: 500 });
```
